        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\n> Patch Set 5:\n> \n> > Patch Set 5:\n> > \n> > seems like these 2 files are still getting added in the working directory causing INFO.yaml to not be the only file in the job\n> > 12:50:29 warning: CRLF will be replaced by LF in scripts/policy/policy-distribution/config/distribution/csar/sample_csar_with_apex_policy.csar.\n> > 12:50:29 The file will have its original line endings in your working directory.\n> > 12:50:29 warning: CRLF will be replaced by LF in scripts/policy/policy-distribution/config/distribution/temp/sample_csar_with_apex_policy.csar.\n> > 12:50:29 The file will have its original line endings in your working directory.\n> \n> Yep\n> \n> I tried to unzip/rezip the csar files on a Linux machine (csar are just archive files). I hoped it would have removed the unexpected char.\n> https://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/integration/csit/+/100077\n> unfortunately it has no effect, so I do not know how to go further\n\nI think it was more about the contents of the archive that the archive itself. Inside there were two file with CRLFs - i replaced them with LFs, please see https://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/integration/csit/+/100241\n\nLet's merge it and retry with this one.",
